    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) and **Kyle Tucker** (78.89). **Gunnar Henderson** occupies the top spot in the order against a favorable matchup with Roupp; his efficiency is bolstered by a significant 16% park adjustment and an aggressive lead-off slot, making him our premier play. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker**\u2014assuming the projected #2 hole\u2014benefits from ideal wind conditions and a soft matchup against Kumar Rocker. **Jackson Merrill** also clears the 75-point threshold, as his projected #3 spot in the lineup combined with the SP skill advantage makes him a cornerstone of today's scoring potential despite the slightly negative park factor.\n\nWhile the core is strong, we are closely monitoring the bottom of the lineup due to weather and defensive concerns. **Miguel Vargas** (52.30) and **Josh Lowe** (51.25) are both carrying elevated rain risk (31% and 38% respectively), which could truncate their plate appearances if the games are delayed or called early. The most difficult personnel decision was leaving **Luis Robert Jr.** on the bench; despite his elite speed and the 100% stolen base opportunity afforded by the opposing battery, his 44.27 score was suppressed by a poor dynamic platoon matchup and a low SP skill baseline, keeping him just behind the higher-floor production of **Heliot Ramos** (57.57) and **Andy Pages** (61.85).\n\nLooking at the remaining roster, **Marcell Ozuna** (58.49) continues to provide reliable stability in the UTIL slot, efficiently navigating a challenging matchup against Imanaga. We remain cautious regarding **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who fell well below our 40-point efficiency floor, and **Nolan Schanuel**, whose upside was stifled by a difficult matchup against the formidable Burns. With **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks** anchoring the catching positions with respectable scores above 57, the Waves are well-balanced to capitalize on today's schedule, provided the rain holds off in the games involving **Miguel Vargas** and **Josh Lowe**.",
